00:22:57.890 --> 00:23:00.350
There is one thing which
should give you pause.

00:23:00.350 --> 00:23:03.670
I have discussed, actually,
a single harmonic oscillator.

00:23:03.670 --> 00:23:06.510
What Dave Pritchard
demonstrated was actually

00:23:06.510 --> 00:23:08.300
two harmonic oscillators.

00:23:08.300 --> 00:23:12.250
The harmonic oscillator has
an x motion and a y motion.

00:23:12.250 --> 00:23:14.810
However, you can
say, this was just

00:23:14.810 --> 00:23:17.120
sort of a trick for
the demonstration,

00:23:17.120 --> 00:23:19.370
because when you have
a circular motion,

00:23:19.370 --> 00:23:21.970
initially, you
have the sine omega

00:23:21.970 --> 00:23:26.744
and the cosine omega 0 component
present simultaneously.

00:23:26.744 --> 00:23:28.410
And you can see what
happens to the sine

00:23:28.410 --> 00:23:30.970
and the cosine component
in one experiment.

00:23:30.970 --> 00:23:33.181
So in that sense, he did
